The paper is about a system and techniques for learning linear predictors with convex losses on terascale datasets. This falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) in arXiv. The paper also involves the use of a cluster of machines, which could fall under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper deals with large datasets, which could fall under the categories of data mining (cs.DM) or computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
